data.title: QCY to launch Track S10 smartwatch for athletes, promises enhanced fitness with precision and power.
data.description: In Dongguan, China, on February 27, 2026, QCY introduced the QCY Track, a state-of-the-art sports smartwatch designed to elevate athletes' fitness experiences. Renowned for high-performance wearables, QCY has developed the QCY Track to cater to the precise needs of users seeking power and endurance in their workouts. This groundbreaking smartwatch is equipped with cutting-edge features that set it apart from the competition, making it the ultimate choice for athletes looking to enhance their training sessions.

data.title: Digital Dentistry Market to grow at 9.62% CAGR to reach USD 16.67 billion by 2031; Restorative Dentistry share at 34.54% in 2025.
data.description: In Hyderabad, India, a recent report from Mordor Intelligence indicates significant growth in the digital dentistry market. Starting at USD 9.61 billion in 2025, it is projected to rise to USD 10.53 billion in 2026, with further growth expected to reach USD 16.67 billion by 2031. This suggests a considerable compound annual growth rate over the forecast period.

data.title: Stores.com, Inc. becomes a multi-brand e-commerce platform serving 17+ million customers, unifying different brands.
data.description: A company based in Dallas, announced on February 26, 2026, that it has rebranded itself as Stores.com, Inc. This new identity brings together several e-commerce platforms including MorningSave, Meh, SideDeal, and Shop Univision. The company, previously known as Mercatalyst, has undergone a transformation to streamline its operations. Stores.com, Inc. now operates as a single entity, providing a unified online shopping experience to its customers.

data.title: Kanazawa Biyori showcases "Godzilla Expo" tracing 70 years of Japanese pop culture legacy. Feb. 26, 2026.
data.description: The Godzilla Expo in Kanazawa, Japan showcases the 70-year journey of the iconic monster and the development of Japanese visual culture. This expo is being held in Kanazawa and offers insights into the evolution of Godzilla over the years. Kanazawa Biyori, a local information platform, is hosting the event. The expo provides a glimpse into the history of Godzilla, a beloved figure in Japanese pop culture. The event is a testament to the enduring popularity of Godzilla, highlighting its significance in shaping contemporary art and entertainment. The expo aims to attract both fans of Godzilla as well as enthusiasts of Japanese visual arts.
